<<<api>>>: Map.keySet
<<<code>>>: public static boolean containsKeyStartingWith(Map<String, Integer> map, String prefix) {
    for (String key : map.keySet()) {
        if (key.startsWith(prefix)) {
            return true;
        }
    }
    return false;
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
    Map<String, Integer> myMap = new HashMap<>();
    myMap.put("abcd", 10);
    myMap.put("efgh", 20);
    myMap.put("ijkl", 30);
    
    System.out.println(containsKeyStartingWith(myMap, "abc")); // true
    System.out.println(containsKeyStartingWith(myMap, "xyz")); // false
}
<<<explanation>>>: You can iterate over the key set of the map and use the startsWith() method to check if each key starts with the given prefix. If a key is found that matches the condition, return true. If no matching key is found, return false.
